Comment: 0,0:11:55.26,0:11:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,12:00
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ED
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.86,0:00:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear viewers, feast your eyes upon this ultimate super-lightweight machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.87,0:00:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This state-of-the-art aerofoil able to convert even a crosswind to a forward thrust...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.86,0:00:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This saddle of pure molded carbon-fiber with no synthetic leather...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.87,0:00:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This pursuit of function and form that has merged into a single work of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.45,0:00:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It goes without saying that to obtain such a machine required much sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.52,0:00:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ignoring my studies, laboring at part-time jobs,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.86,0:00:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,sparing not a second for anything other than my time on the bike...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.55,0:00:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I risked it all to obtain this machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.88,0:00:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this weekend is the Shimanami Cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.68,0:00:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My win there is almost guaranteed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.95,0:00:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And at the end of my winning run I'll finally be greeted by that rose-colored campus life!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.92,0:00:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, can you bring it up? It's open...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.18,0:00:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am prepared for any contingency.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.10,0:00:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This lock is unbreakable, save for using a hydraulic cutter...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.83,0:00:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.71,0:00:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my bicycle!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.19,0:00:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't steal away my two years!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.28,0:00:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.73,0:00:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And just like that, the crystallization of my past two years goes down the drain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.99,0:01:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are called the Cheery Cycle Cleanup Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.07,0:01:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A mysterious autonomous circle that regulates illegal bicycle parking.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.54,0:01:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first they were a group staffed by volunteers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.51,0:01:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,diligently giving their time to maintain the campus,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.02,0:01:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but in recent years they've taken on a strange look,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.29,0:01:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and forcibly remove any bicycle just a tad outside the designated area...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.28,0:01:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And those bicycles are never to be seen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.04,0:01:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rumors are that they end up at bicycle rental shops around Kyoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.40,0:01:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or are transported across the Sea of Japan and sold to that country in the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.18,0:01:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lately they've expanded their influence beyond the campus to the entire city of Kyoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.66,0:01:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so one cannot let down one's guard even when venturing off-campus.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.68,0:01:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\c&H52368F&}"Watch out for this guy!"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.68,0:01:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\c&HA4A09E&}"Never forgive! Cycle Cleanup Corps"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.75,0:01:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are the hated enemy of all Kyoto college students,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.64,0:01:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and a threat to our peaceful daily lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.19,0:01:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why has such a thing happened to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.12,0:01:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is necessary for me to question the one responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.10,0:01:33.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is responsible for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.20,0:03:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\c&H6C00C6&\fad(200,0)}J{\c&H000000&}-pwq
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.63,0:03:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I was a brand-spanking new freshman university student
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.46,0:03:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and before my eyes were innumerable open doors to that rose-colored campus life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.21,0:03:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, ever since I learned I'd passed the entrance exam
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my heart had already been set on the allure of a single circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.23,0:03:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that circle's name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.59,0:03:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fad(200,1400)\bord0\c&HBF4F9A&}"Cycling Club Soleil"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.74,0:03:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There lay my future of pure, sparking gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.21,0:03:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Together with the raven-haired maidens in love rendezvous' fierce contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.55,0:03:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the situation called for it, I'd even be willing to let them ride sitting behind me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is what I, an idiot beyond all redemption, had thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.57,0:03:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Icarus's wings were made of hardened wax melted after he single-mindedly flew straight toward the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.22,0:03:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I in pursuit of that rose-colored campus life was indeed no different,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.49,0:03:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the Cycling Club was a club in name only; it was more like a hard-core cycling team.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.50,0:03:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was cast quickly into despair,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.15,0:03:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and before my feet was a creature with a face like a fish-man just risen from the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.76,0:04:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fiend! Sink back into the ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.99,0:04:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You say some pretty mean things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.29,0:04:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am your compatriot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.50,0:04:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was my first contact with Ozu, as well as worst contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.76,0:04:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what they find fun about rotating their legs so fast they wear away the cartilage?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.02,0:04:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do something more fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.46,0:04:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.15,0:04:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go on a run.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.37,0:04:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.76,0:04:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you resist it, there's no escaping your fate!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.83,0:04:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Training was as harsh as you could imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.78,0:04:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was with the belief that I could overcome the suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.33,0:04:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and reach my rose-colored future that I turned the pedals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.08,0:04:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the world of "roadies," only the fast are recognized and praised.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.83,0:04:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speed is king! Speed is cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.34,0:04:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In high school I didn't belong to any sports clubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.59,0:04:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, I did as few activities as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.84,0:04:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and just stayed cooped up with a bunch of other layabout guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.34,0:04:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So a full-blown athletic team was far too heavy a burden for me to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.76,0:04:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even attempting to train,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.60,0:04:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with my feeble constitution there was no certainty of improvement to begin with,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.01,0:04:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and of course there was no way I'd place well in any competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.52,0:05:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so I shuffled along, wasting my freshman year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.65,0:05:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As usual all you're eating is chicken like a damn fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.31,0:05:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, this is the best source of protein!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.99,0:05:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, my... Must be a struggle for a poor fellow like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.11,0:05:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of chicken, how about letting me eat some salted tongue with green onions?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.55,0:05:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How 'bout you eat some of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.36,0:05:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu never showed his face in the circle, but he'd frequently show up in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.87,0:05:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fad(200,200)\c&HCBE0C3&\3c&H75653C&}"Don't be such a picky eater!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.13,0:05:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fad(200,0)\c&HA7D4EB&\3c&H5652C8&}"Eat it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.19,0:05:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Because someone called Ozu's "Master" lives on the second floor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.95,0:05:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of this boarding house, and it seems Ozu comes to visit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.64,0:05:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I surmised he was probably a master at telling lewd jokes or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.89,0:05:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyebrows are raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.80,0:05:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why so tense?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.94,0:05:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! I have no interest in wasting my time like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.84,0:05:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How cruel. I put a lot of effort into enjoying wasting my college years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.59,0:05:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you have no right to criticize me on that front.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.97,0:05:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.03,0:05:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hold me back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.70,0:05:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God damn him...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.12,0:05:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fad(200,0)\bord1\c&H000000&\3c&HD9F3FA&\be3}"Bicycle Club"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.19,0:05:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.96,0:06:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In there was a cornucopia of information about all possible kinds of aerodynamic bicycle parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.19,0:06:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no physical strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.72,0:06:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, how about I do battle with the specs of my bicycle?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.98,0:06:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it not a path of escape, even for a weak person such as myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.51,0:06:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having seen the light, in my second year I embarked on a complete change of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.55,0:06:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking back on it now, it was only the beginning of yet greater unhappiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To get your hands on a good bicycle takes money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.15,0:06:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A reduction of a mere 1 or 2 grams requires an immense amount of funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.61,0:06:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Replacing the wheels, tires, and shoes with lighter versions...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.86,0:06:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The handlebar, the stem, a compact crank...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.62,0:06:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For me to obtain a somewhat decent bicycle,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.61,0:06:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I left my studies to the side and dove into every part-time job there was,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even dabbling in some illegal work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.10,0:06:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I became nothing more than a saving fiend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.27,0:06:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And finally in the winter of my second year, taking loans from my friends and acquaintances,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.73,0:06:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got my hands on the full-spec machine I had been dreaming of.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.38,0:06:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What lightness!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This bike is, indeed, my wings!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt that I could fly anywhere with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.89,0:06:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I had already heard the rumors of the Cheerful Cleanup Corps,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.23,0:06:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I took extreme caution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.13,0:07:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so enamored with my new bicycle I'd take her out with me wherever I went.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.31,0:07:05.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about this, Manami.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.51,0:07:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had only let my guard down for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.41,0:07:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't expected the Cleanup Corps to go to such lengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.63,0:07:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would never see my beloved wheels again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.29,0:07:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this who I am now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.06,0:07:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the two years I have left, will I stay such a weakling?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.27,0:07:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could not shut my eyes from that reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.13,0:07:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But nor could I stand to look on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.79,0:07:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.26,0:07:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.56,0:07:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you gone nuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.77,0:07:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. On the contrary, I have seen the error of my ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.29,0:07:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had lost sight of something important.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.20,0:07:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bought two years ago at the university co-op,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.64,0:07:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my Manami had been with me through all my joys and sorrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.94,0:08:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, once mad with visions of road bikes, would no longer be led astray.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.91,0:08:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami is for me, my true life-partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.67,0:08:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\c&H18243C&\3c&HFFFFFF&}"Shimanami Cup"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.66,0:08:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But fate soon tore Manami and I apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.78,0:08:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami... Have you seen my Manami?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.63,0:08:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't even consider it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.18,0:08:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems Manami was not considered a participating bike
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.18,0:08:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and was transported to the finish area by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.88,0:08:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the time I figured that out, a great deal of time had passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.95,0:08:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I started the race four hours late and it was already after lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.34,0:08:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Shimanami Cup goes from Onomichi to Shikoku, crossing the bridges from island to island.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.27,0:08:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After crossing one bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.57,0:08:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you run along the coastline of the island, then climb up onto another bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.57,0:08:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it's a strenuous up-down course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.57,0:08:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami, why must you be so heavy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.38,0:08:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder where all the other racers are?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.99,0:08:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or wait, is the race even still going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.25,0:08:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.78,0:08:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? There's still people out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.35,0:08:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need any entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.65,0:08:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though my only goal now was to stay on the course,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.02,0:08:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as night fell I began to lose sight of the course indicators.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.84,0:09:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For what reason was I racing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.41,0:09:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For what reason did I even go to college?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.16,0:09:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manami? What the hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.05,0:09:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a cheap-ass basket-bike!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.45,0:09:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Continuing with the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.81,0:09:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Today in Hiroshima prefecture, the 10th annual Shimanami Cup was held in Onomichi city.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.21,0:09:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The 240 participants put on a fierce race,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.56,0:09:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and the winner with a splendid victory was Kyoto's Higuchi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.42,0:09:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the crystallization of my past two years!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.00,0:09:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.58,0:09:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}"I worked hard for this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.32,0:09:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm very happy I could be victorious for my disciple who always cheered me on," he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.96,0:09:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, enough! I'm going home!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.98,0:09:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where had all this energy I'd expended the whole time vanished to?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.27,0:09:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This violates the conservation of energy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.61,0:09:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does not compute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.56,0:09:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this not a blasphemy of modern physics?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.38,0:09:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While I was thinking of such things, morning dawned, then night fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.25,0:09:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then morning again, then night, and when I came to, I had reached Kyamachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.24,0:10:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your face is a face of extreme impatience... You are unsatisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.99,0:10:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can sense your fiercely earnest talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quickly I did tip my hat to the old woman's keen insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.25,0:10:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, I sense there is an opportunity you can't let pass by.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Opportunity?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.94,0:10:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This opportunity is always dangling in front of your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.26,0:10:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please grab it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.26,0:10:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be 3,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.93,0:10:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You raised the prices again? And damn that was quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.55,0:10:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed that I had somehow fallen into the sea of worthlessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.85,0:10:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or perhaps I had never even taken off to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.51,0:10:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end I was fated to waste away my college life just as Ozu had said.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.93,0:10:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for abducting you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.58,0:10:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking you to my circle's shack.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.58,0:10:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a serious favor to ask you, Senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.03,0:10:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.34,0:10:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-san was a student in the engineering department one year below me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.79,0:11:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The previous year she was the sole female member registered to Soleil,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.24,0:11:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and amazingly won the overall victory at a road race held in Keage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.47,0:11:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to use the prize money for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.31,0:11:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason for me to answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.66,0:11:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had sturdy legs and an air that didn't let others get near her,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.69,0:11:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but she had no real interest in races and quit Soleil.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.58,0:11:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She invested all the prize money in her current circle, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.47,0:11:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.20,0:11:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for the shady look of the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.59,0:11:43.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.52,0:11:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You? You're the dropout from Soleil?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.86,0:11:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.82,0:11:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our club president.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.35,0:11:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, you really do have a feeble body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.35,0:11:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're exactly the kind of man perfect to become a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.62,0:11:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Become a bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.03,0:11:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to our Birdman Team!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.58,0:12:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weight, 59 kilograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.94,0:12:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chest, 80 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.02,0:12:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Waist, 70 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.62,0:12:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, you have the ideal body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.83,0:12:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.87,0:12:15.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-kun is our star engineer, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.42,0:12:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she seems to be interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.91,0:12:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have the airframe almost completed, as you can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.54,0:12:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But no one in the team is suitable to pilot it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.13,0:12:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to do anything in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.50,0:12:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So will you pilot it, with that perfect body you have right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.56,0:12:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to get in that plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.83,0:12:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm a complete weakling. I even dropped out from Soleil...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.87,0:12:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.75,0:12:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need our pilot to be as frail as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.86,0:12:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's not all, but you are definitely our ideal pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.27,0:12:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no special training you will need.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.88,0:12:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simply come to the competition as you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.08,0:12:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just take care of your body so you don't get the flu, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.23,0:13:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a sudden development.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.14,0:13:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It did feel a bit like I was forced into it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.61,0:13:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and isn't this just a nice way of saying "you're a stone falling into a lake"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.11,0:13:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Birdman contest is a cruel game where you pedal and pedal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.34,0:13:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until you inevitably drop into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.58,0:13:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it didn't have to be me; it could have been anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.68,0:13:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And isn't it really scary to head straight into the sea from such a height?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.18,0:13:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unbearable! I can't take losing anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.33,0:13:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was spring of last year, during the road race on Keage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.61,0:13:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had taken off with a good speed at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.86,0:13:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I immediately got winded, and was staring up at the canal incline.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.99,0:13:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power plant over there is quite wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.41,0:13:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's full of dubious machines, and stirs up my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.25,0:13:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's especially lovely during sakura season.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.49,0:13:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-san, shouldn't you be in a hurry?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.56,0:13:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the favorite to win the women's race?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.56,0:13:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.67,0:13:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I'll be off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.83,0:13:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sakura are very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.43,0:13:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so Akashi-san won not only the woman's race, but the overall victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.18,0:13:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then I saw dangling from Akashi-san, the Mochiguman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:01.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They come in sets of five, so it seemed like she had lost one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.27,0:14:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards I came across it, and had continuously forgotten to return it till today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.74,0:14:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This opportunity is always dangling in front of your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.49,0:14:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This body has already crashed once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.62,0:14:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Falling is something I have firsthand knowledge of.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.79,0:14:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I need to do is grit my teeth and launch with a shout.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.61,0:14:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then Akashi-san will surely come to me after I've fallen, with a smile on her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.29,0:14:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then afterwards, I'll sit behind Akashi-san as she rides up the sakura-lined incline!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.12,0:14:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Can I allow myself to be addled by such feelings?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.64,0:14:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your dreams shouldn't be so flimsy, weak, and limp noodled!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.76,0:14:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really okay to lower my future to such a shameless fate?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.34,0:14:34.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To no longer shoot for the sun, but to live lazily on the ground? How is that Icarus?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.20,0:14:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd just be some kid with ugly-ass wings!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.95,0:14:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wavering in the gap between reality and fantasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.08,0:14:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,exhausted by the tumultuous developments of the past few days
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.00,0:14:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my no-rest, no-sleep return from Shikoku,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.60,0:14:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fell to sleep like a sack of potatoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.52,0:14:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you keep up with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.78,0:14:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This man is named Jougasaki, and is president of the Move Circle "Misogi".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.86,0:14:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a man that lives for working out and women's boobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.21,0:14:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I asked him to teach me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.48,0:15:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, I'd made my decision!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.91,0:15:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd fly farther than anyone, higher than anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.29,0:15:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And on the dawn of my victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.48,0:15:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-san will be sitting on the back of Minami as we ride up the sakura-lined incline!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.76,0:15:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up. Victory is everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.60,0:15:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not allow you to run from a battle and live aloof like that Higuchi guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.81,0:15:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're a man, then grab victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.69,0:15:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grab victory, and grab women's tits!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.81,0:15:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jougasaki-senpai's teachings were actually pretty clear-cut,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.30,0:15:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my motivation rose to higher and higher levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.32,0:15:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Birdman contest was even televised, and the place for the circle to shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.75,0:15:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I won, then I would no doubt gain the attention
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.22,0:15:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of raven-haired maiden from all around Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.64,0:15:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet I'd need to broaden my field of vision to other women than just Akashi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.08,0:15:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is a trial all winners must face!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.80,0:15:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being the hero sure is tough!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.97,0:15:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What have you done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.17,0:15:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said you were fine the way you were!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.13,0:15:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now you've got muscles!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.10,0:16:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's ruined!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.25,0:16:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.28,0:16:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-kun's plane is designed with extremely sensitive aviation tolerances!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even a 10-gram difference in the pilot would mean redoing the entire blueprint!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.95,0:16:15.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ruined! It's all ruined!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.42,0:16:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough! Akashi-kun, you be the pilot after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.83,0:16:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and your muscles can get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.35,0:16:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I already had my hands full thinking up countermeasures to the Cleanup Corps!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.66,0:16:27.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.46,0:16:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-kun, you hurry back to work, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.30,0:16:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for getting you involved in this weird stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.26,0:16:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize too, for not living up to your expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.38,0:16:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, actually the problem was that you far surpassed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.40,0:16:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Birdman is, after all, an absurd goal that goes against the reason of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.64,0:16:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I was thinking that the pilot should be a person
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.13,0:16:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with a soul charred by idleness and wasted passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.91,0:16:59.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that after you finished the Shimanami Cup on a basket-bike,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.55,0:17:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you came all the way back from Shikoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.91,0:17:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an incredible waste of energy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.44,0:17:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, that wasn't exactly my intention...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.88,0:17:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I asked you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.92,0:17:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the idea that you'd go so far as to train didn't figure into my calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.39,0:17:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I still have a long way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.31,0:17:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize, but I have to redo the design now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.76,0:17:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.48,0:17:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I knew it I had come to the Keage Incline.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.29,0:17:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had prayed to come here with Akashi-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.43,0:17:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now I felt like the rose-colored campus life was slipping yet even farther away,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.30,0:18:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my heart wept within me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.28,0:18:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'd be better off flowing down and trying and make my name
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.50,0:18:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as an Egg-Pumpkin youkai that lives in lake Biwa...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.55,0:18:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Cleanup Corps!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.73,0:18:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man in the trench coat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.49,0:18:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ozu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.37,0:18:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.89,0:18:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, you caught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.41,0:18:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.13,0:18:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it a secret, 'kay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.68,0:18:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an important source of funds for the Secret Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.87,0:18:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Akashi-san's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.73,0:18:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in recession, so bicycles alone aren't cutting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.38,0:18:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.31,0:18:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A certain person up north is looking for a plane much like this to play with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.38,0:18:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just going to crash into Lake Biwa anyway, so this is a far better use, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what about my bike?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one that stole it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.77,0:18:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really concern myself with each one individually.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.37,0:18:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.92,0:19:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's how I show my love, so grab it while you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.01,0:19:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it doesn't matter which path you take,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.96,0:19:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll keep ending up right where you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.78,0:19:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.60,0:19:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be so bad to give yourself up and go with the flow?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.72,0:19:14.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're connected by the black thread of fate, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.29,0:19:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.84,0:19:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got debts, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.61,0:19:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go around Kyoto collecting bicycles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.15,0:19:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only if I can aim mainly at couples riding two to a bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.31,0:19:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing! You do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.36,0:19:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.51,0:19:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the jig's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.12,0:19:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Akashi-san is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.85,0:19:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell anyone about the Cleanup Corps, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.57,0:19:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Might be bad for your health....
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.83,0:19:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.80,0:19:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:19:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the trench coat man from the Cycle Cleanup Corps!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:20:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! That's not it! Akashi-san, this is a misunderstanding!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.84,0:20:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it, The Cheery Cycle Cleanup Corps are actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.08,0:20:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.80,0:20:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Explain it to me now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.67,0:20:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.57,0:20:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.88,0:20:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, where are the brakes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.20,0:20:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.53,0:20:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.87,0:20:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jump off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.76,0:20:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate I'll crash into the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.46,0:20:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no choice but to try pedaling and fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.21,0:20:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's the time for my training to pay off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.29,0:20:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.47,0:20:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the pedals?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.14,0:20:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akashi-san, where are the pedals?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.95,0:20:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.64,0:20:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the free-flying category!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.85,0:21:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It finally dawned on me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.57,0:21:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that this was all a truly wasted effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.19,0:21:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps this all started from the moment I considered the cycling club.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.38,0:21:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had joined some other circle, I would have surely spent quite a different two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.83,0:21:16.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meeting Ozu was clearly the greatest catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.07,0:21:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could Icarus have ridden the wind had he not tried to so hard to flap his wings?
